{
  "texts": [
    "Comparison of existing and proposed methods for autonomous driving simulation.ChatSim that achieves automatic simulation editing via language commands and integrates external digital assets to enhance realism and flexibility.",
    "In ChatSim, we integrate McNeRF, a novel neural radiance field designed to leverage multi-camera inputs for high-fidelity rendering.Lighting estimation.",
    "Lighting estimation focuses on assessing the illumination conditions of a real-world environment to seamlessly integrate digital objects.",
    "Early methods [37,38] for outdoor environments use explicit cues like detected shadows on the ground.",
    "Recent works usually adopt learning-based approaches [27,31,32,39,43,78] by predicting different lighting representations like spherical lobes [10,43], light probes [39], environment map [57,59], HDR sky model [31,68,78] and lighting volume [68]."
  ]
}